        name='retrieve_information',
        args='{"prompt":"Find segment-level disclosures for AI and Connectivity in {{spacex_s1}}, including revenue, cost of revenue, operating expenses, capital expenditures, and any segment financial tables. Also include any discussion of AI infrastructure buildout, data center investments, or GPU purchases."}',
        parsed_args={
            'prompt': 'Find segment-level disclosures for AI and Connectivity in {{spacex_s1}}, including revenue, cost of revenue, operating expenses, capital expenditures, and any segment financial tables. Also include any discussion of AI infrastructure buildout, data center investments, or GPU purchases.'
        }
    ),
    tool_output=ToolOutput(
        output='Based on the provided financial document chunks, here are the segment-level disclosures for the AI and Connectivity segments, including financial tables, drivers of revenue and expenses, capital expenditures, and infrastructure investments.\n\n---\n\n### **1. Connectivity Segment Disclosures**\n\nThe Connectivity segment operates a worldwide high-speed, low-latency broadband network powered by thousands of Starlink satellites in Low-Earth Orbit, delivering connectivity to consumer, enterprise, and government customers.\n\n#### **Financial Performance & Drivers (MD&A)**\n*   **Revenue:** Growth has been primarily driven by Starlink subscriber base growth and increasing enterprise and government adoption.\n    *   *Q1 2026 vs. Q1 2025:* Revenue increased $782 million, from $2,475 million to $3,257 million.\n    *   *2025 vs. 2024:* Revenue increased $3,788 million, from $7,599 million to $11,387 million (a 49.8% year-over-year growth).\n    *   *2024 vs. 2023:* Revenue increased $3,730 million, from $3,869 million to $7,599 million.\n*   **Cost of Revenue:** Increases are driven by higher depreciation as the number of satellites placed into orbit grows, higher operating expenses, and volume spend on Starlink Kits as deliveries increase. \n    *   *Q1 2026 vs. Q1 2025:* Increased $437 million (to $1,651 million).\n    *   *2025 vs. 2024:* Increased $1,153 million (to $5,921 million).\n    *   *2024 vs. 2023:* Increased $1,982 million (to $4,768 million).\n*   **Profitability:** The segment generates strong operating income and Segment Adjusted EBITDA. In 2025, income from operations was $4,423 million and Segment Adjusted EBITDA was $7,168 million (an 86.2% YoY growth), benefiting from network efficiency and major cost reductions in user terminal production.\n\n#### **Revenue Disaggregation (Connectivity)**\n| Revenue Type | 2025 | 2024 | 2023 | Q1 2026 | Q1 2025 |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **Consumer** | $7,208 | $4,830 | $2,817 | $2,148 | $1,492 |\n| **Enterprise & Government** | $4,179 | $2,769 | $1,052 | $1,109 | $983 |\n| **Total Connectivity** | **$11,387** | **$7,599** | **$3,869** | **$3,257** | **$2,475** |\n\n---\n\n### **2. AI Segment Disclosures**\n\nThe AI segment operates a vertically integrated AI platform spanning a frontier LLM (Grok), AI solutions for consumer and enterprise customers, and X (a real-time information platform). The company acquired xAI in February 2026.\n\n#### **Financial Performance & Drivers (MD&A)**\n*   **Revenue:** Driven by X and Grok subscriptions, advertising sales, and data licensing arrangements. \n    *   *Q1 2026 vs. Q1 2025:* Revenue increased $91 million, from $727 million to $818 million.\n    *   *2025 vs. 2024:* Revenue increased $581 million, from $2,620 million to $3,201 million.\n    *   *2024 vs. 2023:* Revenue decreased $341 million (from $2,961 million to $2,620 million) due to a decrease in advertising sales, partially offset by X subscriptions and data licensing.\n*   **Cost of Revenue:** Includes infrastructure costs (data center facilities, lease/hosting, energy, bandwidth, depreciation of servers/networking equipment, public cloud hosting), revenue share expenses, payment processor fees, payments to creators, and amortization of acquired intangibles. \n    *   *Q1 2026 vs. Q1 2025:* Increased $5 million (to $456 million).\n    *   *2025 vs. 2024:* Increased $491 million (to $2,178 million) due to higher infrastructure and cloud computing costs.\n*   **Research & Development:** R&D expenses relate to training the Grok frontier model, developing next-generation AI products, and data center costs. \n    *   *Q1 2026 vs. Q1 2025:* Increased $1,471 million (to $2,379 million) driven by **depreciation of GPU hardware**, cost of cloud computing, and data center infrastructure expenses due to AI data center expansions.\n    *   *2025 vs. 2024:* Increased $3,888 million (to $5,064 million) driven by GPU hardware depreciation and cloud computing costs.\n*   **Profitability:** The AI segment is in an early stage of development, generating significant operating losses. In 2025, loss from operations was $(6,355) million and Segment Adjusted EBITDA was $(1,237) million. The company expects a multi-year investment horizon before deployments translate into sustained positive Segment Adjusted EBITDA.\n\n#### **Revenue Disaggregation (AI)**\n| Revenue Type | 2025 | 2024 | 2023 | Q1 2026 | Q1 2025 |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **Advertising** | $1,844 | $1,728 | $2,323 | $343 | $443 |\n| **AI Solutions & Infrastructure** | $1,357 | $892 | $638 | $475 | $284 |\n| **Total AI** | **$3,201** | **$2,620** | **$2,961** | **$818** | **$727** |\n\n---\n\n### **3. AI Infrastructure Buildout & Capital Expenditures**\n\nThe AI segment is undergoing a massive infrastructure buildout to address a $26.5 trillion potential market opportunity. Capital expenditures are scaling rapidly to deploy power, compute, and terrestrial/orbital data centers.\n\n*   **Capital Expenditures by Segment (in millions):**\n    *   **AI CapEx:** $463 (2023) → $5,633 (2024) → $12,727 (2025) → $2,567 (Q1 2025) → **$7,723 (Q1 2026)**\n    *   **Connectivity CapEx:** $2,455 (2023) → $3,498 (2024) → $4,178 (2025) → $814 (Q1 2025) → **$1,332 (Q1 2026)**\n*   **Data Centers & GPU Hardware:** The company is expanding its terrestrial data centers and plans to launch orbital data centers. R&D and Cost of Revenue are being heavily impacted by the depreciation of GPU hardware and public cloud hosting costs. \n*   **Capitalized Interest:** For the year ended December 31, 2025, the company capitalized $169 million of interest related to the construction period for significant long-term AI infrastructure data center projects.\n\n---\n\n### **4. Consolidated Segment Financial Tables**\n\n#### **Year Ended December 31, 2025**\n| (in millions) | Space | Connectivity | AI | Total Reportable Segments |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **Revenue** | $4,086 | $11,387 | $3,201 | $18,674 |\n| Cost of revenue | 1,352 | 5,921 | 2,178 | 9,451 |\n| Research and development | 3,004 | 575 | 5,064 | 8,643 |\n| Selling, general, and administrative | 349 | 468 | 1,827 | 2,644 |\n| Restructuring charges | — | — | 487 | 487 |\n| Impairment | 38 | — | — | 38 |\n| **Total costs and expenses** | 4,743 | 6,964 | 9,556 | 21,263 |\n| **Income (loss) from operations** | (657) | 4,423 | (6,355) | (2,589) |\n| *Supplemental Info:* | | | | |\n| Depreciation and amortization | $757 | $2,376 | $3,568 | $6,701 |\n| Capital expenditures | $3,832 | $4,178 | $12,727 | $20,737 |\n\n#### **Year Ended December 31, 2024**\n| (in millions) | Space | Connectivity | AI | Total Reportable Segments |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **Revenue** | $3,796 | $7,599 | $2,620 | $14,015 |\n| Cost of revenue | 1,541 | 4,768 | 1,687 | 7,996 |\n| Research and development | 1,835 | 453 | 1,176 | 3,464 |\n| Selling, general, and administrative | 375 | 333 | 1,105 | 1,813 |\n| Restructuring charges | — | — | 213 | 213 |\n| Impairment | 24 | 39 | — | 63 |\n| **Total costs and expenses** | 3,775 | 5,593 | 4,181 | 13,549 |\n| **Income (loss) from operations** | 21 | 2,006 | (1,561) | 466 |\n| *Supplemental Info:* | | | | |\n| Depreciation and amortization | $637 | $1,508 | $1,679 | $3,824 |\n| Capital expenditures | $2,032 | $3,498 | $5,633 | $11,163 |\n\n#### **Year Ended December 31, 2023**\n| (in millions) | Space | Connectivity | AI | Total Reportable Segments |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **Revenue** | $3,557 | $3,869 | $2,961 | $10,387 |\n| Cost of revenue | 1,669 | 2,786 | 1,655 | 6,110 |\n| Research and development | 1,538 | 381 | 186 | 2,105 |\n| Selling, general, and administrative | 351 | 233 | 1,081 | 1,665 |\n| Restructuring charges | — | — | 237 | 237 |\n| Impairment | — | — | 3,775 | 3,775 |\n| **Total costs and expenses** | 3,558 | 3,400 | 6,934 | 13,892 |\n| **Income (loss) from operations** | (1) | 469 | (3,973) |